OL,7,FShe says she went to work on Monday
OL,8,Fmorning and was "in tears" as soon as
OL,9,Fshe walked in.
OL,11,FDescribing the moment the staff were
OL,12,Ftold about the closure, she says:
OL,14,F"I've never ever cried so much in one
OL,15,Fday, I didn't think a job would impact
OL,16,Fme mentally that much.
OL,18,F"You've made so many connections with
OL,19,Fyour customers, our regulars who I
OL,20,Fmight never see again.
